 pip dependency (lizard) behind an optional `[metrics]` extra, mirroring the existing `grounding`/`agents` extras. scc and jscpd are EXTERNAL CLIs (not pip deps) detected at runtime. Core-only install must import cleanly and degrade code_health to Unavailable.\n\n## Review-driven corrections\n- Register `metrics` in `src/rebar/_optional.EXTRAS` (probe module + install blurb) — the friendly \"install rebar[metrics]\" guidance and `guard_import(extra=\"metrics\")` both require the entry; `guard_import` raises `OptionalDependencyError` (it does not return), so adapters CATCH it and convert to Unavailable.\n- `src/rebar/metrics/analyzer.py` is CREATED by blocker 3b30 — this ticket EXTENDS it (adds the guarded lizard import path), it does not create/own it.\n- Respect the import-linter optionality ban-list: `import rebar` / `import rebar.metrics` must stay dependency-free (lizard imported lazily inside the analyzer, never at package import).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `[project.optional-dependencies] metrics = [\"lizard>=1.23\"]` + comment (scc/jscpd = external CLIs); `metrics` added to `_optional.EXTRAS`.\n- [ ] lizard reached via `guard_import(..., extra=\"metrics\")`; missing extra -> `OptionalDependencyError` caught -> Unavailable(reason names the extra), no ImportError escapes, `import rebar[.metrics]` stays dependency-free.\n- [ ] Core-only install: `rebar metrics` does not crash; code_health reports Unavailable.\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Test simulating missing extra -> Unavailable; import-linter/optionality check still green.\n\n## Dependencies: 3b30 (interface). Recorded edge: depends_on 3b30.\n## Files likely touched: pyproject.toml, src/rebar/_optional.py, src/rebar/metrics/analyzer.py (extend), tests/unit/metrics/test_metrics_extra_guard.py (new)\n## Estimated scope: S-M","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"pyproject.toml","reason":"add [project.optional-dependencies] metrics = lizard; comment scc/jscpd as external CLIs"},{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/analyzer.py","reason":"route lizard import through guard_import(extra=metrics)"},{"path":"src/rebar/_optional.py","reason":"reuse guard_import; confirm friendly missing-extra guidance"},{"path":"tests/unit/metrics/test_metrics_extra_guard.py","reason":"new: missing extra -> Unavailable, no ImportError escapes"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","3b30-2168-ba16-41fc"],["parent","839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051"]],"parent_id":"839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051","parent_status_uuid":"37a55131-7c3a-40ca-9dcf-4a8c137531a2","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","code-health"],"ticket_id":"9597-1b85-d2ab-4eed","ticket_type":"story","title":"Add the optional [metrics] extra + lazy import guard (core stays dependency-free)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["fba3d081-2bd1-4094-86a1-4de17c335b98","9cd277b2-6b48-43d0-88f2-b7d8d135be1b","01528e83-3478-4d04-9af2-a243790a7614","92fc4acb-e908-4c27-b8a2-ab4b6c317ee9","18ab84a2-833d-4134-8ce9-59a11cb2b9cc","37a55131-7c3a-40ca-9dcf-4a8c137531a2","f106e1da-1c16-4099-ad25-25f52dea4d8a"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784827006922576002,"uuid":"38ab1948-165d-4500-b437-3c9dac95e589"}